SENATE RESOLUTION 373
By Rose
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Andrea Sena, 2026
Valedictorian of Munford High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Andrea Sena is one such exceptional student, who was recently named
Valedictorian of the 2026 graduating class at Munford High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Sena has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Andrea Sena has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, her display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well for her
future success; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Sena's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for her
family, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Andrea Sena's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of our respect,
admiration, and commendation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we commend and honor the
2026 Munford High School Valedictorian, Andrea Sena, on her impressive academic
achievement and extend to her our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
